HEADWORD: Rooky
<hw>Rook"y</hw> <pr>(-⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Roky</er>.]</ety> <def>Misty; gloomy.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Light thickens, and the crow⟦br⟧
Makes wing to the <qex>rooky</qex> wood.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Some make this Shakespearean word mean ⟦ldquo⟧abounding
in rooks.⟦rdquo⟧</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

